       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt" "tests/spec/parse-negative-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Unterminated block comments produce lexical errors; block comment markers are strict-case (`OBTW`/`TLDR` only); comma-inline OBTW/TLDR handoff is supported per examples, while `TLDR` with trailing statement text requires comma/newline boundary."))
 #hash((id . "fmt.preprocessing-order-adjudication")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 27)
       (clause . "Formatting controls (comments, comma soft-breaks, continuation) require a deterministic preprocessing order.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/lexer.rkt" "src/lolcode/parser.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/parse-negative-test.rkt" "tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Adjudication: lexer performs newline normalization/comment handling/continuation/comma conversion with string shielding, then parser applies phrase rewrites; ordering-sensitive regressions include inline TLDR comma handoff and continuation shielding cases."))
 #hash((id . "parse.longest-match-keyword-phrases")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 431)
       (clause . "Multiword and punctuated keyword forms are parsed by exact phrase tokens (e.g., O RLY?, WTF?, IM OUTTA YR).")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/lexer.rkt" "src/lolcode/parser.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/parse-negative-test.rkt" "tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Adjudication: punctuated keywords require canonical token shape (`RLY?`, `WTF?`), phrase collapse for IM IN/IM OUTTA applies only to same-line token pairs, and keyword recognition is strict-case for direct keyword tokens."))
 #hash((id . "program.envelope-hai-kthxbye")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
