       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Adjudication: general execution uses lexical frames (main/function locals). In object-function context, bare IT resolves in method activation-local ordinary scope (never receiver-slot/global alias)."))
 #hash((id . "var.declare-basic")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 117)
       (clause . "I HAS A <variable> [ITZ <value>] declaration.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/parser.rkt" "src/lolcode/runtime.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt" "tests/spec/conformance-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Declaration + initializer semantics implemented with boxed lexical bindings."))
 #hash((id . "var.declare-literal-type-inference")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 123)
       (clause . "Literal initializers instantiate the corresponding primitive type; identifier/expression initializers use the resulting value.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/runtime.rkt" "src/lolcode/runtime/value.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Declaration initializer values are used directly; literal forms produce their corresponding value domain (NUMBR/NUMBAR/TROOF/YARN/NOOB)."))
 #hash((id . "var.identifier-shape")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 111)
       (clause . "Identifiers must start with a letter, followed by letters/digits/underscores only.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/lexer.rkt" "src/lolcode/parser.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/parse-negative-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Identifier domain adjudication is ASCII-leading-letter + ASCII letter/digit/underscore tail (`^[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9_]*$`): mixed-case/underscore forms are accepted, while non-ASCII direct identifiers and malformed forms (_x, x-y, ++, etc.) are rejected at parser/runtime identifier gates."))
 #hash((id . "var.keyword-token-reservation-adjudication")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 111)
       (clause . "Identifier shape text overlaps with keyword token forms (e.g., AN, MKAY).")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/parser.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/parse-negative-test.rkt" "tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Adjudication: strict parser reserves keyword token lexemes in direct identifier positions to avoid grammar ambiguity with keyword-delimited forms. Ambiguity examples: `VISIBLE SMOOSH x AN y MKAY` (AN separator vs identifier argument) and `VISIBLE SMOOSH \"A\" MKAY` (explicit closer vs identifier with implicit EOL closure). Keyword-shaped names remain available through `SRS` where 1.3 allows dynamic identifiers."))
 #hash((id . "var.declare-typed-default")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 126)
       (clause . "I HAS A <variable> ITZ A <type> default values.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/parser.rkt" "src/lolcode/runtime/value.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt" "tests/spec/fixtures/manifest.rktd"))
       (notes . "ITZ A declaration defaults are restricted to TROOF/YARN/NUMBR/NUMBAR/NOOB/BUKKIT. Prototyping remains disambiguated as ITZ LIEK A <parent> (plain) and ITZ A <parent> SMOOSH ... (mixin); bare ITZ A <non-built-in> declarations are rejected. Bare ITZ TYPE-word remains a legal TYPE-literal expression initializer."))
 #hash((id . "var.declare-uninitialized")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 140)
       (clause . "I HAS A <variable> initializes to NOOB.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/runtime.rkt" "src/lolcode/runtime/env.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Uninitialized declarations bind to NOOB."))
 #hash((id . "var.function-shares-namespace")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 145)
       (clause . "Function types behave like variables and share the same namespace.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/runtime.rkt" "src/lolcode/runtime/env.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Same-scope redeclaration now errors across variable/function bindings; assignment may still overwrite an existing function binding as shown by spec example."))
 #hash((id . "var.srs-any-identifier-position")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 170)
       (clause . "SRS may be used anywhere a regular identifier is expected.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/parser.rkt" "src/lolcode/runtime.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Supported across declaration/assignment targets, slot access, function/method/object names, loop labels/updaters, method-call names, and object name/parent positions. Parameter binders remain direct-only (`YR <ident-token>`), and dynamic `SRS` parameter names are parse-rejected."))
 #hash((id . "var.declare-optional-a-for-srs")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 189)
       (clause . "A becomes optional in declaration when using SRS target.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/parser.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Variable declaration accepts omitted article in strict 1.3 (e.g., I HAS ..., I HAS SRS ...); if an article is present there, it must be A (AN rejected), while other forms keep explicit-article requirements per grammar text."))
 #hash((id . "var.assignment-r")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 205)
       (clause . "<variable> R <expression> assignment.")
       (status . implemented)
       (code-refs . ("src/lolcode/parser.rkt" "src/lolcode/runtime.rkt"))
       (test-refs . ("tests/spec/parse-negative-test.rkt" "tests/spec/runtime-core-test.rkt" "tests/spec/conformance-test.rkt"))
       (notes . "Assignments require lvalue targets (identifier/SRS target or slot chain), mutate existing bindings only, and raise runtime error for undeclared identifier assignment."))
 #hash((id . "stmt.assignment-operator-shape")
       (spec-version . "1.3")
       (source-file . "spec/upstream/lolcode-spec-v1.3.md")
       (source-line . 411)
       (clause . "Assignment statements are of form <variable> <assignment operator> <expression>.")
